      <h5 class="mb-2">The "Problem"</h5>
      <p>Administrators were being saddled with a major headache if they wanted to recognize years of service at their organization using Workhub’s Rewards program: Track years of service… somewhere?... and hand-bomb it into Workhub with a manual point adjustment.</p>
      <p>The Rewards program allows organizations to award "points" to workers who complete tasks (watching training videos, uploading certificates, participating in surveys, + much much more). These points are used on Workhub to redeem tons of cool products. If you'd like to learn more, please checkout my <a href="/case-studies/wh-rewards-catalog">Workhub Rewards catalog refresh case study</a>.</p>
      <p>The benefits of recognition are well known at Workhub, retention skyrockets at orgs that dole out even small rewards. So we decided to make the bet - we were going to explore interest in a bespoke anniversary component in Workhub.</p>
      <p>It would help administer similar programs, boost conversions by Workers who will now have to pick and item on their anniversary (not just squirrel away the points!), and continue to grow our recognition component stable.</p>
      <p>Two questionnaires were sent out to customers currently using recognition components in Workhub and another was set out to the broader Workhub community. The results were positive and we decided to move forward.</p>
    </div>
